ZH: 明天我们一家要去扫祖坟。
EN: Tomorrow, my family is going to sweep the ancestral graves.
ZH: 他们每年都会扫墓祭祖。
EN: They sweep the graves and pay respects to their ancestors every year.
ZH: 扫墓是祭扫节日的重要部分。
EN: Tomb-sweeping is an important part of the Qingming Festival.
ZH: 春节前，许多人都会提前扫墓。
EN: Before the Spring Festival, many people will sweep the tombs early.
ZH: 在扫墓时，要三鞠躬，三跪九叩。
EN: When sweeping the tombs, you should bow three times, kneel three times, and kowtow nine times.
ZH: 这个节日的主要活动是扫墓和祭祖。
EN: The main activities of this holiday are tomb-sweeping and ancestor worship.
ZH: 扫墓是一种传统习俗，许多人都积极参与。
EN: Tomb-sweeping is a traditional custom that many people actively participate in.
ZH: 扫墓是为了纪念已故的亲人。
EN: Tomb-sweeping is to commemorate deceased loved ones.
ZH: 他们开始扫墓时，天空下起了小雨。
EN: As they started to sweep the tombs, it started drizzling.
ZH: 这个周末我们一起去扫墓吧。
EN: Let's go sweep the tomb together this weekend.
ZH: 扫墓活动过程中，会烧纸、烧香。
EN: During the tomb-sweeping activity, paper money and incense are burned.
ZH: 他们在扫墓时唱着祭祖歌。
EN: They sang ancestor worship songs while sweeping the tombs.
ZH: 扫墓不仅是纪念亲人，也是缅怀历史。
EN: Tomb-sweeping is not only to commemorate loved ones, but also to remember history.
ZH: 她提着鲜花去扫墓。
EN: She carried flowers to sweep the tomb.
ZH: 扫墓的习俗有着悠久的历史。
EN: The custom of tomb-sweeping has a long history.
ZH: 扫墓的时候，要向祖宗敬茶、敬酒。
EN: When sweeping the tomb, you should offer tea and wine to the ancestors.
ZH: 他们认为扫墓是传承家族文化的一种方式。
EN: They believe that tomb-sweeping is a way to pass down family culture.
ZH: 每年清明节，全家都会一起去扫墓。
EN: Every Qingming Festival, the whole family goes together to sweep the tombs.
ZH: 扫墓不仅是悼念逝去的人，也是尊重祖先。
EN: Tomb-sweeping is not only to mourn the deceased, but also to respect ancestors.
